        "body": "No, I am fine with the round divisions generated by _freq_.\r\nMy intent was to fit every repartition types into a single _divisions_ parameters while keeping the other parameters of course (_npartitions_, _partition_size_, _freq_)\r\n\r\nIt's already allowed to use:\r\n```\r\ndd.repartition(divisions='10MB')      # 10 MB max per partitions, same as partition_size='10MB'\r\ndd.repartition(divisions=42)          # 42 partitions, same as npartitions=42\r\ndd.repartition(divisions=(x, y, z))   # manual partitions\r\n```\r\nSo, I thing we could also add:\r\n```\r\ndd.repartition(divisions='10D')                       # same as freq='10D'\r\ndd.repartition(divisions=pd.Timedelta(hours=12))      # same as freq=pd.Timedelta(hours=12)\r\n```\r\n\r\nBecause _divisions_ is the first positionnal args, this will lead to shorter and still very readable code:\r\n```\r\ndd.repartition('10MB') \r\ndd.repartition(42)\r\ndd.repartition('10D') \r\n```\r\n\r\n",
